
[1]hunting

   HUNT'ING, ppr. Chasing for seizure; pursuing; seeking; searching.

   HUNT'ING, n. The act or practice of pursuing wild animals, for catching
   or killing them. Hunting was originally practiced by men for the
   purpose of procuring food, as it still is by uncivilized nations. But
   among civilized men, it is practiced mostly for exercise or diversion,
   or for the destruction of noxious animals,as in America.

   1. A pursuit; a seeking.
